# Neural Style Transfer
Neural style transfer is an optimization technique used to take two images,a content image and a style reference image (such as an artwork by a famous painter)—and blend them together so the output image looks like the content image, but “painted” in the style of the style reference image.
# Approach 
Steps to implement nueral style transfer
> Extract content from the content image, 4_2 convolution layer of pre trained vgg19
network is used as content extractor
> Extract style from the style image. Here we interpret style as the texture of the
image, and not the pixel values. We calculate a feature map i.e. the gram matrix using
1_1 ,2_1 ,3_1 ,4_1 ,5_1 with varied style weight constant for each layer.
> find the content loss and the style loss, further find a combined loss function with
two hyper parameters.
> minimising the loss function and producing the final output image
